job_description:
Position Description:The Accounting and Reporting Manager is responsible for managing and coordinating the accounting and reporting process of Group subsidiaries and at consolidated level. She/He also oversee the preparation of periodic financial reports, including consolidated financial statements, to provide internal and external stakeholders with a clear and accurate view of the company's financial health. Additionally, this role plays a crucial part in strategic decision-making by providing financial analysis and insights based on consolidated dataPosition Responsibilities:* Financial Consolidation: Supervise and coordinate the consolidation process of financial accounts from various subsidiaries and entities of the company. Ensure the integrity of consolidated financial data in accordance with accounting standards and company policies ;
* Financial Reporting: Prepare and present periodic individual and consolidated financial reports (monthly, quarterly, annually) to management and shareholders. Analyze significant variances and trends, and provide clear and concise explanations of financial results ;
* Financial Analysis: Conduct in-depth analyses of consolidated financial performance to identify improvement opportunities, potential risks, and key growth areas. Provide recommendations to support strategic decision-making;
* Compliance and Accounting Standards: Ensure that the consolidation and reporting operations comply with local and international accounting standards and financial regulations ;
* Coordinate the annual local and consolidated audit with external auditors;
* Close collaboration with different accounting firms to ensure the accuracy and completeness of accounting data, social and fiscal taxes;
* Team Management: Supervise and lead a team of finance and accounting professionals dedicated to accounting and reporting. Develop the team's skills and ensure effective communication within the department , other departments and external accounting firm ;
* Process Improvement: Identify opportunities for automation and optimization of accounting and reporting processes to enhance operational efficiency and reduce closing times;Qualifications:* University degree in finance, accounting, or related field;
* Significant professional experience (8 to 12 years) in financial accounting, consolidation and reporting, with experience in team management ;
* Excellent knowledge of international accounting standards (IFRS, ISA, etc.) and relevant tax and social laws ;
* Proven ability to analyze and interpret complex financial data ;
* Strong written and oral communication skills, with the ability to present financial information in a clear and understandable manner;
* Ability to work under pressure in a dynamic environment and meet closing deadlines;
* Developed sense of communication in a multicultural context
* Written and oral proficiency in English (Spoken and Written)Preferred Skills* Ability to work independently with minimal direct supervision; * Held a similar position with an international firm in the past in the early stages of growth; * M&A integration experience is a nice to have.
